      <center><img src="resources/7058de84ab6505fcdd739bb36c1f0695-web.svg"/></center>    </li>  </ol></block>  </mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15925</anchor> <rss>jms-00CE.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-00CE</addr>  <route>jms-00CE.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Unitality of the <link href="jms-00CD.xml" type="local" title="The induced weak successor algebra">induced weak successor algebra</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb{T}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal{C}</tex>, and let <tex>X</tex> be a <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">weak algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb{T}</tex> for which the algebra map is invertible by <tex>{ X } \xrightarrow{{ \pi _{ X } }} { T X }</tex>. Then the <link href="jms-00CD.xml" type="local" title="The induced weak successor algebra">induced weak successor algebra</link> <tex>X ^s</tex> is <link href="jms-00C5.xml" type="local" title="Algebra for a monad">unital</link>.</p>      <block open="open"><headline><b>Proof</b>.</headline>   <p>We are trying to check that the following morphism is an identity:</p>  <center><img src="resources/d4c2905dc6994f8b69cbf0a5e5d024cb-web.svg"/></center>  <ol>    <li>We unfold the definition of the algebra map <tex>\alpha _{ X ^s }</tex>.
      <center><img src="resources/df063430eb2e85989d87430775a41266-web.svg"/></center>    </li>    <li>We use the unit law for <tex>\mathbb{T}</tex>.
      <center><img src="resources/2bce4749b0870142b6d4c68a12929f32-web.svg"/></center>    </li>    <li>Finally, we use the fact that <tex>\pi _{ X }</tex> is inverse to <tex>\alpha _{ X }</tex>.
      <center><img src="resources/e9eb3146cf77a42b60370734008be59b-web.svg"/></center>    </li>  </ol></block>  </mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15926</anchor> <rss>joyal-moerdijk-1995.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Reference</taxon> <addr>joyal-moerdijk-1995</addr>  <route>joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml</route> <date><year>1995</year>  </date> <authors><author><link href="andréjoyal.xml" type="local">André Joyal</link></author><author><link href="iekemoerdijk.xml" type="local">Ieke Moerdijk</link></author> </authors> <title>Algebraic set theory</title> <meta name="venue">Cambridge University Press</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree></references></backmatter></tree>